<item>
            <title>[AVRO-675] Bytes and fixed setters don&apos;t update datum size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-675</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The setter methods for bytes and fixed datum instances don&apos;t update the size field.  So, for instance, if you create a datum:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;avro_datum_t  datum = avro_wrapbytes(NULL, 0);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then later you update that datum to point to a different buffer:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;avro_wrapbytes_set(datum, &quot;hello&quot;, 5);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you write that datum out to a file, you&apos;ll get a zero-length value in the output, since the size pointer didn&apos;t get updated from 0 to 5.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
