<item>
            <title>[AVRO-676] Avro IDL can&apos;t process includes from disparate src trees</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-676</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-495&quot; title=&quot;Avro IDL should support includes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-495&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-495&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduced support from includes in IDL. However it turns out that a bug in the implementation, which assumes that the path for the included path is in the same src tree causes it to not support includes from different source trees.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;E.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;src/foo/main/avro/a.genavro&lt;br/&gt;
// something here&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;src/foobar/main/avro/b.genavro&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;protocol foobar {&lt;br/&gt;
  import idl &quot;src/foo/main/avro/a.genavro&quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
  ...&lt;br/&gt;
}.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12475828">AVRO-676</key>
            <summary>Avro IDL can&apos;t process includes from disparate src trees</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/open.png" description="The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.">Open</status>
                    <statusCategory id="2" key="new" colorName="blue-gray"/>
                                    <resolution id="-1">Unresolved</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="acmurthy">Arun C Murthy</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Tue, 5 Oct 2010 00:34:15 +0000</created>
                <updated>Tue, 5 Oct 2010 19:02:34 +0000</updated>
                                            <version>1.4.0</version>
                                                    <component>java</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12917840" author="acmurthy" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 00:51:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Illustrative patch... seems to work for me. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918079" author="cutting" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 17:09:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IDL import statements are relative to the IDL file they&apos;re in:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://avro.apache.org/docs/current/idl.html#imports&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://avro.apache.org/docs/current/idl.html#imports&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is by analogy with CPP:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/cpp/Include-Syntax.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/cpp/Include-Syntax.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, in your example, I believe you should use something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; idl &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;../../../foo/main/avro/a.genavro&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch you&apos;ve provided makes all imports relative to the connected directory of the compiler&apos;s JVM, which is not desired.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918099" author="acmurthy" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 18:19:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the clarification Doug. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I get this error with a relative path:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; idl &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;../../../foo/main/avro/a.genavro&quot;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Embedded error: Error importing ../../../foo/main/avro/a.genavro: java.io.FileNotFoundException: ./../../../foo/main/avro/a.genavro (No such file or directory)
Caused by: org.apache.avro.idl.ParseException: Error importing ../../../foo/main/avro/a.genavro: java.io.FileNotFoundException: ./../../../foo/main/avro/a.genavro (No such file or directory)
	at org.apache.avro.idl.Idl.ImportIdl(Idl.java:320)
	at org.apache.avro.idl.Idl.ProtocolBody(Idl.java:261)
	at org.apache.avro.idl.Idl.ProtocolDeclaration(Idl.java:162)
	at org.apache.avro.idl.Idl.CompilationUnit(Idl.java:49)
	at org.apache.avro.mojo.AvroMojo.execute(AvroMojo.java:153)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have verified that the relative path is correct... am I missing anything? Help? Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918117" author="cutting" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 19:02:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A relative path works for me when I modify a unit test to use one.  Can you provide a test that fails?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
