<item>
            <title>[AVRO-677] Avro schema not properly resolved on data file read.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-677</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Based on the &quot;schema resolution and record names&quot; thread:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/avro-user/201010.mbox/thread&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/avro-user/201010.mbox/thread&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When reading records from a data file of type namespace1.Record1 using a specific reader of type namespace2.Record2, reading succeeds even though schema resolution should fail.  Instead, this should require the use of aliases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll be attaching a code example shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
